column4: hey guys, just installed Feisty on my laptop. But everytime i try to install anything through synaptic it tells me the dependencies "are not installable"
Does the fact that I installed the Alternate Feisty ISO have anything to do with the fact that I can't install anything through synaptic?
no... your sources.list might be faulty. waht do you get when you sudo apt-get update?
oh I see what happened, i installed it over the network and now it's trying to find the updates on the computer I installed it on instead of the Ubuntu repositories
